The positions and coding directions of the 24 genes and open reading frames (ORF) are shown in the schematic genome map (Fig. 2
). The locations, as well as lengths of each gene (nucleotide and amino acid) and their G + C content, are indicated in Table 3
. The ITR regions were located on left and right ends. IVa2, polymerase, protein precursor (pTP), DNA binding protein (DBP), U exon and ORF8 were transcribed leftward, and sialidase, ORF4, 52K, pIIIa, III (penton), pVII, pX, pVI, hexon, protease, 100K, 22K, 33K, pVIII, E3 region, fiber and ORF7 were transcribed rightward.

The viral genome and phylogenetic analysis showed that SPSAdV belonged to genus Siadenovirus in the family Adenoviridae (Fig. 3
). At the nucleotide level, the SPSAdV pol, penton base and hexon genes exhibited somewhat higher sequence similarity of 73.8%, 79.2% and 77.5% with RAdV-1 than with THEV (68.3%, 75.4% and 74.9%) (Table 4
).
